OVERHEARD IN #dataviz AT STACKSWORTH INC.

@intern: "Should I use Canvas or SVG for this 200-point scatterplot?"
@svgArtist: "SVG."
@intern: "But I read that Canvas is faster—"
@svgArtist: "For 200 points? SVG. You get hover events, CSS styling, accessibility, and the ability to right-click inspect every single dot. Canvas gives you a flat image that you can't interact with without reimplementing half the browser's event system."
@intern: "When would I use Canvas then?"
@svgArtist: "When you have 50,000 points and SVG brings your browser to its knees. Until then, SVG. Always SVG."
@transitionEase: "And with SVG you can transition each dot individually. With Canvas you're redrawing the entire frame. SVG transitions feel organic. Canvas transitions feel mechanical."
@intern: "ok SVG it is"
